{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":77043,"duration_api_ms":108044,"num_turns":5,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"3818aab9-c348-4148-a868-d5770b155e3f","total_cost_usd":0.36225134999999997,"usage":{"input_tokens":753,"cache_creation_input_tokens":26139,"cache_read_input_tokens":78532,"output_tokens":2551,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":26139,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":76,"outputTokens":5368,"cacheReadInputTokens":237631,"cacheCreationInputTokens":33118,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.09207660000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":753,"outputTokens":2551,"cacheReadInputTokens":78532,"cacheCreationInputTokens":26139,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.27017475,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All five amendments identify genuine, verified defects. The code confirms each claim: deterministic backoff without jitter (dc9c6dba), tmux session leak on cancel() failure due to premature HashMap removal (fe174b87, c240683f), fire-and-forget process reaping that silently drops kill errors and deregisters the child before teardown (fc18423c), and over-broad ENOENT→BinaryNotFound classification (bfd7d960). Each fix is well-scoped, addresses a real operational failure mode, and carries low implementation risk.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-11-dc9c6dba","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: backoff_for_attempt() at retry_policy.rs:106-113 computes `base * 2^(attempt-1)` capped at backoff_cap with zero randomization. The system runs concurrent panel members sharing API backends (engine.rs:4620 calls this per-cursor), so synchronized retries will produce thundering-herd amplification. Adding ±20-30% uniform jitter is a textbook fix, trivial to implement (one rand call), and breaks no existing tests since the backoff values are deterministic today only by accident, not by contract."},{"amendment_id":"fr-11-fe174b87","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: tmux.rs:540 calls self.cancel() on timeout. cancel() at line 633 calls take_active_session() which does sessions.remove() at line 247, immediately deregistering the session. If the subsequent SIGTERM (line 640) or SIGKILL (line 664) fails, cancel() returns Err but the session is already gone from the HashMap — orphaned and unreachable for future cleanup. The timeout handler at line 540 logs the error and continues to return FailureClass::Timeout. The proposed fallback of directly calling kill_session on the still-in-scope session name is practical and addresses the immediate leak without requiring structural changes to cancel()."},{"amendment_id":"fr-11-fc18423c","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: at process_backend.rs:1052, spawn_background_reap is fire-and-forget (tokio::spawn). At line 1053, remove_child_if_same runs immediately — before the reap task has a chance to kill the process. spawn_background_reap at lines 1477-1480 discards both force_kill() and wait() errors with `let _`. If kill fails, the hung process continues running but the adapter has forgotten the handle, and the retry loop will spawn a second process potentially against the same workspace. This is a concrete process-leak and workspace-conflict bug. Synchronous teardown confirmation or at minimum error propagation is the correct fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-11-c240683f","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified and complementary to fe174b87. The root cause is that cancel() at tmux.rs:633-636 performs take_active_session() (destructive HashMap remove) as its first action, before any cleanup is attempted. This violates the invariant that a resource should only be deregistered after successful teardown. The structural fix — keeping the session tracked until teardown succeeds, or re-inserting on failure — prevents the orphan state at its source. Both this and fe174b87 should be implemented: fe174b87 as a defensive fallback in the caller, and this as the root-cause fix in cancel() itself."},{"amendment_id":"fr-11-bfd7d960","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified: process_backend.rs:998-999 maps all ErrorKind::NotFound from Command::spawn() to FailureClass::BinaryNotFound. On Linux, spawn() returns ENOENT (NotFound) for at least three distinct cases: (1) the executable doesn't exist, (2) the working directory doesn't exist, (3) a script's shebang interpreter is missing. Cases 2 and 3 are not binary-missing failures and may be transient (e.g., a race in workspace setup). Classifying them as BinaryNotFound causes them to be treated as terminal, skipping the retry budget. A pre-check (e.g., Path::exists on the binary) before committing to BinaryNotFound would correctly disambiguate these cases."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"eb91d48b-f34b-4e49-b232-b674ccff351a"}
